settings.title: How it works
settings.content:
Take 1 gummy daily at or around the time of a dinner (or snack), or as directed by your healthcare practitioner. Keep out of reach of children. Store tightly sealed in a cool, dry place without direct sunlight.

Our bodies produce endocannabinoids, naturally, which are neurotransmitters that bind to cannabinoid receptors in your nervous system. Studies & Science have shown that CBD can help reduce chronic pain by affecting endocannabinoid receptor activity, reducing inflammation, and interacting with neurotransmitters controlling your overall mood, comfort, appetite and more.

You can take our Rest Support + at any point in the day that works best for you and your needs, but we recommend you take it at or around the time of a meal or snack. Why do you ask? The absorption of the essential fat-soluble vitamins is naturally supported by the proximity of a meal or snacke with some fat content.

settings.text_cont: Thiamine plays an important role in converting carbohydrates into energy. Without thiamine, the nervous system can’t function and everyday abilities like walking, cognition and speech are impaired
Riboflavin works to reduce oxidative stress and inflammation of nerves, which are contributors to migraine headaches.
Niacin (vitamin B-3) is often part of a daily multivitamin, but most people get enough niacin from the food they eat.
In addition to playing a role in the breakdown of fats and carbohydrates for energy
Vitamin B-6 (pyridoxine) is important for normal brain development and for keeping the nervous system and immune system healthy.
Folate (vitamin B-9) is important in red blood cell formation and for healthy cell growth and function.
Vitamin B12, or cobalamin, is naturally found in animal foods. It can also be added to foods or supplements.
Vitamin A, also known as retinol, has several important functions.
Vitamin D3 is best known for strengthening your bones, which it does by helping the body absorb calcium and phosphorus from food
Phytonadione (vitamin K1) is a medication used to treat and manage vitamin K deficiency, which is a significant risk factor for intracranial hemorrhage and other bleeds
It contributes to skin health and bone metabolism, promotes proper brain function and prevents heart-related diseases.
